logy political science economics anthropology public policy law health services research and related fields the fellowship carries a stipend between $40000 and $45000 depending on experience with $2500 for research expenses the fellow will be expected to be in residence for at least three academic quarters beginning fall 2011 he or she is required to present research findings in a center seminar and to release at least one working paper in the ahpp working paper series on health and demographic change in the asia pacific the fellow may participate in other activities at the freeman spogli institute for international studies such as the weekly research in progress seminars at the center for health policy applicants should submit two letters of recommendation a curriculum vitae and a short research statement not to exceed six double spaced pages by january 15 2011 address all materials and queries to lisa lee shorenstein aparc stanford university encina hall room e301 stanford ca 94305 6055 650 725 2429 voice 650 723 6530 fax llee888 stanford edu search ahpp fellowship news shorenstein postdoctoral fellowship program grows march 9 2012 shorenstein aparc news new asia health policy postdoctoral fellows march 16 2011 shorenstein aparc news postdoctoral fellow in asia health policy combines legal and economic expertise march 5 2009 shorenstein aparc announcement young kyung do awarded inaugural postdoctoral fellowship in comparative health policy february 11 2008 shorenstein aparc news support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 725 2429 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
